 :tx/rationale "Set t-0210660b title=C8-FIX-3: Filter braid-self-referential entities from seed in external projects. Genesis bootstrap entities (crate info, Store::genesis patterns, cargo commands) must not appear in seeds for non-braid projects. BACKGROUND: Store::genesis() creates bootstrap entities describing braid's own crate structure (Cargo.toml deps, module layout). When seed assembles context for an external project, these braid-internal entities pollute the context and confuse agents (they see Rust crate info for a Go project). FIX: (1) In assemble() (seed.rs), detect if the project is external: check if any :extractor/* or :policy/* datoms exist that are NOT braid-default. (2) If external, filter out entities whose :db/ident starts with known braid-internal prefixes: :crate/*, :module/*, :cargo/*. (3) Alternatively, tag genesis entities with :provenance/source = braid-bootstrap and filter by provenance in seed assembly. (4) The provenance approach is cleaner and more C8-compliant — it doesn't hardcode namespace names. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid seed in braid project: includes all entities (no filtering). (B) braid seed in Go project: excludes crate/module/cargo entities. (C) Shared entities (schema, policy) appear in both. (D) No false positives (user-created entities with :crate/ prefix preserved). DEPENDS-ON: C8-FIX-1. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs (genesis)"
